The Nigeria Customs Service (NCS) male team and the Nigeria Security Civil Defence Corp (NSCDC) female team yesterday both emerged winners of the 2019 national Volleyball Premier League after 10 days of scintillating performance. NSCDC defeated the all conquering Customs male team 3-2 (21-25, 25-18, 22-25, 25-22, 15-9), but it was too little, too late as NCS retained their title, having won their four previous games. NCS finished with 30 points, followed by NSCDC -24, Kano pillars -23,  Police-22, Immigration-19, UCEM -2 points. In the female category, NSCDC outclassed the sleeky NCS ladies 3-0 (25-19, 25-23, 25-18) to dethrone them as champions. The NSCDC ladies emerged champions with 32 points followed by NCS -28 points, Army-20 points , Immigration -10 points, Kada Emeralds-9 points and Benue Queens-3 points. NCS player, Isaac Geofrey, who won the best male block in the tournaments while speaking to LEADERSHIP sports, expressed his joy for winning the championship adding that they will put up an impressive performance when they represent Nigeria at the continental club championship next year. “We promised to win the title at the end of the tournaments and we have done that all thanks to the Nigeria Customs service for their support ”he said. “We are now going to shift all our attention to the continental club championship coming up next year and we promised to do the nation proud” he added. The premier league which started on November 21 ended yesterday at the indoor sports hall, package B of the Moshood Abiola stadium in Abuja The male teams that participated in the league are NCS, NSCDC, Police Nigeria Immgration Service (NIS), Kano Pillars, Plateau Rocks, UCEM and Famous spiders. The female teams are- NCS, NSCDC, NIS, COAS-Army, Benue Queens, Delta Force and Kada Emeralds.